content.description: Start the same as Short Long, just skip the big move by using dish out to left, continue up just left of tree.
Do Mulletino, then drop off at big jug that starts the upper crux.
Stand start on small ledge, then climb right facing slight groove to a fun HP40 top out. Welcome to HP40
content.location: A lone boulder about 25-30 feet behind Mulletino boulder (behind Rubberneck). This problem is on the backside of this boulder.

content.description: Start on jug under roof, long move to good hold then up on tiny crimps.
content.location: Middle of broad side of Mulletino Boulder facing the parking lot. Just in front of large stone.

content.description: Sit start on jugs far under the overhang and traverse out crack same as Mulletino. After gaining far side of large roof feature, deviate left from Mulletino to pinch rail, make big move to crimp at edge of roof, move into slopers on vertical side and through jugs to top out
content.location: Mulletino boulder. Behind the ten-pins area next to four wheeler path

content.description: Start is low with hand crack, exit out of roof and climb face/groove
content.location: To the left of Wrong Long, back side of Boulder.

content.description: Sit start off rail, work through a bubbly face.
Sit start in the crack at the back of overhang. Climb out jugs and climb right to arete, to sketchy top-out.
content.location: Look for the overhang on the Mulletino boulder, close to the dirt road.

content.description: Grab the start holds of Low Down, get on, then say "This block is on, right?" Regardless of anyone's answer, surprise everyone by pulling your whole torso onto the block and get into a coffin position. From here, walk backwards on your shoulders until you make it 5 feet to the even narrower side of the block. Use your abs and toe cams to reach out to any of the lowest sloper holds on the right side. Either finish by topping out on Low Down or go even farther right and top out in the water groove. If you top out Low Down I'd sign your scorecard if it was me because I'd respect you for finding this beautiful line. If you're not in a crack, are you even climbing? Maybe the block could use some dusting but if you do that first people won't be as surprised when you squeeze onto it so avoid that.
content.protection: A few pads to lay out in front of Low Down V4 so people think that's what you're about to get on, or if you're alone then you don't need pads for the traverse because you can't fall out of the coffin so you just use one for the top out. The perfect crime.
content.location: The non contrived version of Low Down V4 on The Mulletino Boulder.

content.description: Hard, LOW traverse on sloper-jugs to a committing topout. Start on the jugs left of the block and traverse out right.https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iVWUduTze8w&t=41s
content.protection: A pad and a spotter to drag it as you go.
content.location: It's on the Mullentino Boulde Boulder. Walk around until you =see a small boulder, thats the side you see a fallen block. You'll see jugs close to the block. USING THE BLOCK IS NOT PART OF THE PROBLEM!!!

content.description: Sit start under short roof. Reach out for crimp with yer right paw, and then finish up face with good holds.
Sit start base of a somewhat water groove with a crimper for yer left paw and yer right paw on an undercling. Move into slight groove and then to holds that are just right of this groove.
Same start as Ghetto Superstar, but at the triangle hold, make a long move out and right to break in lip.
content.location: Same as G.S. then trends right.

content.description: Sit start in a low break. Take the sloping edge to a smiley face edge ( crux . Using the smiley face edge climb left on decent crimps to chicken head. Then climb crimpers on face. ( Mossy jug on the left is off )
content.location: Mullentino Boulder: Close to dirt road, the boulder with overhang towards road.

content.description: Sit Start. Match on scar and then reach for jug and mantle out to finish.
Start on bumps and climb semi-rail
content.location: On the boulder to the right of Low Down

content.description: Huge boulder next to the dirt road behind Ten Pins area/with a overhang facing the road.
